I've been running some experiments with this code, looking at availability issues. I've been downing the node via sqshell, rebooting, etc..  Mostly it seems to be pretty solid - thanks!  One issue keeps coming up though:  When I up a node in sqshell after a failure, I consistently see that RMS processes don't get restarted.  Then, because the RMS processes don't get started, connectivity won't restart the missing mxosrvrs
